using { ShortageService as service } from '../shortage-service';



annotate service with @odata @rest @hcql @graphql ;
annotate service with @mcp;
annotate service with @mcp.instructions: 'Material availability monitoring and shortage escalation service for MachBau GmbH, a machine manufacturer in NRW, Germany. MachBau produces industrial machines. Each machine (Production Order) requires multiple components (Materials). The system monitors stock levels and flags shortages that require human procurement approval. Entities: Materials - Product master data from SAP S/4HANA (API_PRODUCT_SRV). Key: Product (e.g. 21, 68, 71) as numeric strings. ProductType: FERT = finished good, HALB = semi-finished, ROH = raw material, HERS = manufactured part. ProductGroup: classification group (e.g. L001). Expand to_Description for human-readable names (field: ProductDescription). Expand to_Valuation for pricing (fields: StandardPrice, MovingAveragePrice, Currency). MaterialsStock - Real-time warehouse stock per material, plant, and storage location from API_MATERIAL_STOCK_SRV (entity A_MatlStkInAcctMod). Key: Material + Plant (composite). MatlWrhsStkQtyInMatlBaseUnit: the on-hand quantity. MaterialBaseUnit: unit of measure (EA, ST, KG). InventoryStockType: empty string = unrestricted/available, 01 = blocked/not available, 02 = quality inspection/not available. InventorySpecialStockType: empty string = ordinary warehouse stock, O = consignment, E = project stock, K = customer stock. ProductionOrders - Manufacturing orders from API_PRODUCTION_ORDER_2_SRV (entity A_ProductionOrder_2). Key: ManufacturingOrder (e.g. 1000010). Material: the finished product being produced. ProductionPlant: plant where manufacturing occurs. TotalQuantity: quantity to produce. MfgOrderPlannedEndDate: planned completion date. OrderIsReleased, OrderIsCreated, OrderIsTechnicallyCompleted, OrderIsClosed: boolean lifecycle status flags. Example queries: List products with names - query Materials expand to_Description. Check stock at plant 1010 - query MaterialsStock where Material = 68 and Plant = 1010. Unrestricted stock only - query MaterialsStock where Material = 68 and Plant = 1010 and InventoryStockType = empty string. Released production orders - query ProductionOrders where OrderIsReleased = true. Zero-stock materials - query MaterialsStock where MatlWrhsStkQtyInMatlBaseUnit eq 0. Product pricing - query Materials expand to_Valuation. Tips: Use the describe tool first to discover exact field names and types. Material IDs and Plant codes are strings. Boolean fields (OrderIsReleased etc.) use true/false not strings.';